# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# docupilot-web .dockerignore
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Applies to the `./frontend/docupilot-web` build context. Excluding these
# from the daemon-uploaded context (a) speeds up `docker build` start, and
# (b) ensures the in-image `npm ci` produces a fresh node_modules tree
# rather than copying a host one with native bindings compiled for a
# different platform.

# Host-installed dependencies — must be reinstalled inside the image
node_modules/

# Build outputs — must be rebuilt inside the image
dist/
.angular/

# Logs and temp
*.log
npm-debug.log*
.cache/

# IDE / editor noise
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# Documentation does not belong in the runtime image
*.md

# Secrets / local env files — must never enter an image
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Git metadata (the build context is the project dir; .git lives at
# code/.git so this is mostly defensive)
.git/
.gitignore

# Test-only artefacts — production image does not need them. Note: test
# .spec.ts source IS included in the context because the production
# `npm run build` step does not import them and pruning them here saves
# only a trivial amount of context size while complicating Angular's
# build inputs. Keep it simple and ship the spec files into the build
# stage; they evaporate after `npm run build` anyway because they are
# not referenced from main.ts.
